   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1844-03_page02.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#North-Audley-Street-1_ENK">1 North Audley Street</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                        Sunday Night<lb/>
                  <date when="1844-03-31">Mar 31<hi rend="superscript">st</hi>
                     <unclear>44</unclear>
                  </date>
               </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p><hi rend="underline">Alas!</hi> my dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CaveS1">Lady Dacre</persName>
               <lb/>
                    -- I need say no more --<lb/>
                    for the moment you see<lb/>
                    that one word Alas! you<lb/>
                    know all the rest.<lb/>
                    It is impossible that I<lb/>
                    can avail myself of that<lb/>
                    most gratifying and<lb/>
                    tempting invitation to the<lb/>
               <unclear>Hooo</unclear> which your Ladyship<lb/>
                    and <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BranT1">Lord Dacre</persName> so kindly<lb/>
                    as well as so politely gave<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1844-03_page03.jpg"/>
                    me -- Time! Time! Time!<lb/>
                    I cannot command --<lb/>
                    -- nor can I snatch at<lb/>
                    a pleasure for myself<lb/>
                    at the expense of us all<lb/>
                    I told you &amp; that you were<lb/>
                    so good to listen to &amp; I<lb/>
                    trust to believe -- It was<lb/>
                    all out of <unclear>reels</unclear> and<lb/>
                    perhaps shewed both<lb/>
                    manque d'esprit and<lb/>
                    manque d'usage to lay<lb/>
                    before <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CaveS1">Lady Dacre</persName> and<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BranT1">Lord Dacre</persName> too my letter<lb/>
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1844-03_page04.jpg"/> 
                    domestic <unclear>true</unclear> reasons<lb/>
                    but I am much <choice>
                  <orig>&gt;mista<lb/>
                        -ken</orig>
                  <reg>mistaken</reg>
               </choice> if either of them<lb/>
                    think the worse of me<lb/>
                    for this sincerity and<lb/>
                    for confiding in their<lb/>
                    indulgence</p>
            <lb/>
            <closer>
                    My sister <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">Wilson</persName> begs<lb/>
                    her respects -- &amp; Believe<lb/>
                    me my dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CaveS1">Lady Dacre</persName>
               <lb/>
                    Your obliged<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
